67
00:05:11,189 --> 00:05:17,794
For more details on other fission processes,
we refer you to the video 2.8.

68
00:05:17,794 --> 00:05:21,750
If we consider the parent
nucleus to be at rest,

69
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:27,370
energy conservation gives us a relation
between the masses and energies.

70
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:31,070
Since the number of electrons
is unchanged in the reaction,

71
00:05:31,070 --> 00:05:35,186
you can directly use atomic mass for
this calculation.

72
00:05:35,186 --> 00:05:40,143
T_alpha and T_D are the kinetic
energies of the alpha particle and

73
00:05:40,143 --> 00:05:41,809
the daughter nucleus.

74
00:05:41,809 --> 00:05:47,710
The gain in binding energy that drives
the decay is called the Q value.

75
00:05:47,710 --> 00:05:53,540
And it is converted into the kinetic
energy of the decay products.

76
00:05:53,540 --> 00:06:01,100
An example of the calculation of
T_alpha and T_D is given in video 2.4a.

77
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:04,520
